    body: "Ignatian spirituality is the spiritual tradition flowing from St. Ignatius of Loyola (1491-1556), founder of the Society of Jesus (Jesuits). Its cornerstone is the Spiritual Exercises, a structured program of meditations, contemplations, and rules for discernment designed to help a person order their life according to God's will. Key principles include: 'finding God in all things' (seeing the divine in every aspect of life), the 'magis' (always seeking the greater glory of God), the Examen (a daily prayer reviewing God's presence and one's responses throughout the day), the 'Principle and Foundation' (human beings are created to praise, reverence, and serve God), discernment of spirits (distinguishing between consolation and desolation to recognize God's leading), and 'indifference' (holy detachment from anything that is not God's will). Ignatian spirituality is notably active and apostolic, seeing contemplation and action as inseparable.",
