    body: "The Enthronement of the Sacred Heart is a devotional practice in which a family formally consecrates their home to the Sacred Heart of Jesus by solemnly installing a blessed image (statue or picture) of the Sacred Heart in a prominent place in the home. The practice was developed and promoted by Father Mateo Crawley-Boevey, SS.CC., in the early 20th century with the encouragement of Pope St. Pius X. The ceremony typically involves a priest blessing the image, the family reciting an act of consecration, and enthronement of the image in the living room or another central location. It is not merely decorative; the family commits to living under the reign of Christ's love, practicing daily prayer, and making acts of reparation. The enthronement is renewed annually, often on the Feast of the Sacred Heart.",
