    body: "The Green Scapular was revealed to Sister Justine Bisqueyburu, a Daughter of Charity of St. Vincent de Paul, in a series of visions of the Blessed Virgin Mary beginning in 1840. Unlike cloth scapulars that are worn, the Green Scapular is a single piece bearing an image of Our Lady on one side and the Immaculate Heart of Mary on the other, with the prayer: 'Immaculate Heart of Mary, pray for us now and at the hour of our death.' It was approved by Pope Pius IX in 1863. The Green Scapular is uniquely intended as a tool of intercession: it may be placed in the room, belongings, or clothing of a person for whom one is praying — even without that person's knowledge. The one praying need only recite the associated prayer daily with faith. It is particularly associated with graces of conversion, healing of illness, and return to the sacraments.",
