    body: "Holy wells are natural water sources consecrated by association with a saint, a miraculous event, or longstanding tradition of prayer and healing. They are especially common in Ireland, Scotland, Wales, and Brittany, where Celtic Christianity sanctified pre-Christian sacred springs. Pilgrims visit holy wells to pray, make rounds (circling the well while praying), leave offerings, and sometimes drink or bathe in the water seeking healing. The wells are often decorated with rags, medals, and rosaries left by pilgrims.",
