    body: "Sacred springs in Catholic tradition are distinguished from holy wells by their association with specific miraculous events, particularly Marian apparitions. The most famous is the spring at Lourdes, which appeared at Our Lady's direction when St. Bernadette dug in the mud of the Massabielle grotto in 1858. The Lourdes Medical Bureau has documented numerous inexplicable healings attributed to the water. Other sacred springs exist at sites like Banneux (Belgium) and Knock (Ireland). The water itself is a sacramental, not a sacrament—its power comes from faith and God's free gift.",
